@node Copyright "Copyright"

The Macks Conspiracy own the copyright to Graphic Workbench, but as its
Public Domain in the true sence of the word you are free to copy &
distribute it as long as you make no profit.

We would like to take this opportunity to mention the pictures used in
Graphic Workbench. When this project first started the brief was for around
20-30 pictures the boys figured they could have that many ready no problem
but then the data disk idea took off and the figure quadrupled.
so we scanned the Aminet for some of the best pics available. all of the
pics had readme files and many of the authors refused to give permission for
their artwork to be used without written consent from them, which is fair
enough I suppose. Anyway the pictures we did use were the ones where the
author had no problems about his/her artwork being used as long as it wasn't
in a commercial product. Also where the author had written there name on the
picture it can still be seen and no changes have been made to their pics,
except maybe to flip the image but that doesn't count, does it.
If any artist out there feels we have used their artwork inappropriatly
then we apologise.
@endnode

